    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "A new Colombian pest species of the genus Poecilocloeus Bruner (Orthoptera: Acrididae: Proctolabinae) on coffee, with a key to the Neotropical species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699433>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699437>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699435>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699439>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699441>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699443>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699445>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699447>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699449>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699451>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699453> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699433>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. (male). A) Frons. B) Head and pronotum in lateral view. C) Terminalia, dorsal view. D) Rinsed with KOH, showing the divergent aedeagus valves. E) Terminalia, lateral view. F-G) Phallic complex showing the different positions of the epiphallus and the convergent aedeagus valves. F) Dorsal view. G) Lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699433/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699437>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. (male). A) Adult male, lateral view. B) Dorsal view with right wing spread." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699437/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699435>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. (female). A) Habitus in lateral view. B) Frons. C) Head and pronotum in lateral view. D–F) Terminalia in dorsal, ventral and lateral view respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699435/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699439>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Different stages of development of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. A) First instar. B) Second instar. C) Third instar. D) Fourth instar. E) Fifth instar. F) Sixth instar. G) Adult male. H) Adult female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699439/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699441>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Damage caused by nymphs of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. in the foliage of coffee trees. A-C, E, F) Scrapings on the leaf blade. D) Chewed-on and wilted apical shoots." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699441/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699443>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Damage caused by adults of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. on coffee plants. A) Close-up of leaf damage. B) Scrapings on the bark of stems and branches. C) Damage of ripe fruit. D-E) Damage of unripe and near ripe fruits. F) Fruits with the pulp consumed. G) Coffee fruits with the exocarp and pulp completely eaten off and the grains exposed." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699443/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699445>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Natural enemies of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. A) Leaf mantis Acanthops centralis. B) Leaf mantis Acontista cordillerae. C) Nematode Mermis sp., parasite of P. coffeaphilus adults. D) Assassin bug Zelus vespiformis. E) Entomopathogenic fungi Beauveria bassiana on adult of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus. F) Beauveria bassiana on P. coffeaphilus nymph." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699445/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699447>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Accumulated mortality of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus nymphs with a strain of Metarhizium acridum by the immersion method (T1) and spraying (T2), spraying with a commercial formulation of Metarhizium anisopliae (T3) and control treatment with water (T4)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699447/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699449>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Laboratory pathogenicity tests with entomopathogenic fungi on Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. A) Nymphs in muslin cages. B) Strain of Metarhizium acridum in a PDA growing medium. C-F) Nymphs of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus dead and parasitized with Metarhizium acridum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699449/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699451>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Evaluation of the mortality percentage in adults of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. by the nematode Mermis sp. A) Adults in growing cages. B) Mortality of adults. C) Adults of Mermis sp. emerged from the grasshoppers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699451/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699453>
    dc:description "Figure 12. Main hosts of Poecilocloeus coffeaphilus n. sp. Left: “Cascarillo” Ladenbergia oblongifolia (Rubiaceae). Right: Pat’egallina Oreopanax floribundum (Araliaceae) defoliated by grasshoppers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3699453/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

